name: ObservableList
comment: Represents an observable list of model values. If any items are added, removed, or replaced, then observers that are listening to observe/observe.ChangeNotifier.changes will be notified.

length=.name: length=
length=.comment:
Changes the length of this list.

If newLength is greater than the current length, entries are initialized to null.

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if the list is fixed-length.

length.name: length
length.comment:
Returns the number of objects in this list.

The valid indices for a list are 0 through length - 1.

listChanges.name: listChanges
listChanges.comment:
The stream of summarized list changes, delivered asynchronously.

Each list change record contains information about an individual mutation. The records are projected so they can be applied sequentially. For example, this set of mutations:

var model = new ObservableList.from(['a', 'b']);
model.listChanges.listen((records) => records.forEach(print));
model.removeAt(1);
model.insertAll(0, ['c', 'd', 'e']);
model.removeRange(1, 3);
model.insert(1, 'f');

The change records will be summarized so they can be "played back", using the final list positions to figure out which item was added:

#<ListChangeRecord index: 0, removed: [], addedCount: 2>
#<ListChangeRecord index: 3, removed: [b], addedCount: 0>

observe/observe.ObservableList.deliverChanges can be called to force synchronous delivery.

constructors.comment:
Creates an observable list of the given observe/observe.ObservableList.ObservableList-.length.

If no observe/observe.ObservableList.ObservableList-.length argument is supplied an extendable list of length 0 is created.

If a observe/observe.ObservableList.ObservableList-.length argument is supplied, a fixed size list of that length is created.

from.name: from
from.comment: Creates an observable list with the elements of observe/observe.ObservableList.ObservableList-from.other. The order in the list will be the order provided by the iterator of observe/observe.ObservableList.ObservableList-from.other.

[].comment: Returns the object at the given observe/observe.ObservableList.[].index in the list or throws a dart-core.RangeError if observe/observe.ObservableList.[].index is out of bounds.

[]=.comment: Sets the value at the given observe/observe.ObservableList.[]=.index in the list to observe/observe.ObservableList.[]=.value or throws a dart-core.RangeError if observe/observe.ObservableList.[]=.index is out of bounds.

applyChangeRecords.name: applyChangeRecords
applyChangeRecords.comment: Updates the observe/observe.ObservableList.applyChangeRecords.previous list using the change records. For added items, the observe/observe.ObservableList.applyChangeRecords.current list is used to find the current value.

calculateChangeRecords.name: calculateChangeRecords
calculateChangeRecords.comment:
Calculates the changes to the list, if lacking individual splice mutation information.

This is not needed for change records produced by observe/observe.ObservableList itself, but it can be used if the list instance was replaced by another list.

The minimal set of splices can be synthesized given the previous state and final state of a list. The basic approach is to calculate the edit distance matrix and choose the shortest path through it.

Complexity is O(l * p) where l is the length of the current list and p is the length of the old list.

length=.name: length=
length=.comment:
Changes the length of this list.

If observe/observe.ObservableList.length=.newLength is greater than the current length, entries are initialized to null.

Throws an dart-core.UnsupportedError if the list is fixed-length.

hasObservers.name: hasObservers
hasObservers.comment: True if this object has any observers, and should call observe/observe.ObservableList.notifyPropertyChange for changes.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides observe/observe.ObservableList.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

length.name: length
length.comment:
Returns the number of objects in this list.

The valid indices for a list are 0 through length - 1.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and observe/observe.ObservableList.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the observe/observe.ObservableList.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

[].comment: Returns the object at the given observe/observe.ObservableList.[].index in the list or throws a dart-core.RangeError if observe/observe.ObservableList.[].index is out of bounds.

[]=.comment: Sets the value at the given observe/observe.ObservableList.[]=.index in the list to observe/observe.ObservableList.[]=.value or throws a dart-core.RangeError if observe/observe.ObservableList.[]=.index is out of bounds.

lastIndexOf.name: lastIndexOf
lastIndexOf.comment: Returns the last index in the list a of the given observe/observe.ObservableList.lastIndexOf.element, starting the search at index observe/observe.ObservableList.lastIndexOf.startIndex to 0. Returns -1 if observe/observe.ObservableList.lastIndexOf.element is not found.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
observe/observe.ObservableList.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to observe/observe.ObservableList.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If observe/observe.ObservableList.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of observe/observe.ObservableList.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

notifyPropertyChange.name: notifyPropertyChange
notifyPropertyChange.comment:
Notify that the field name of this object has been changed.

The observe/observe.ObservableList.notifyPropertyChange.oldValue and observe/observe.ObservableList.notifyPropertyChange.newValue are also recorded. If the two values are equal, no change will be recorded.

For convenience this returns observe/observe.ObservableList.notifyPropertyChange.newValue. This makes it easy to use in a setter:

var _myField;
@reflectable get myField => _myField;
@reflectable set myField(value) {
  _myField = notifyPropertyChange(#myField, _myField, value);
}

observed.name: observed
observed.comment: Override this method to be called when the observe/observe.ObservableList.changes are first observed.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

unobserved.name: unobserved
unobserved.comment: Override this method to be called when the observe/observe.ObservableList.changes are no longer being observed.
